properties.Name: BARCA
properties.description:
Area's South-East Entry/Exit Point

Area's South-West Entry/Exit Point

Recommended ENTRY procedure
When flying over BARCA, you should initiate contact with Strejnic Airfield on 131.455 and wait to receive the flight conditions in the area. Entry through this point is performed at 1400ft QNH. The next report from incoming traffic in order to enter south traffic pattern should be made before base if runway in use is 25, or  before downwind if runway in use is 07, unless otherwise instructed by the flight coordinator. 

Recommended EXIT procedure
Leaving the traffic pattern is usually done right before joining the base leg if runway in use is 25, or just before joining downwind, if runway in use is 07, following the way to BARCA in an ascending flight towards a minimum of 1700ft QNH. At the vertical of the locality of Bărcănești, contact Bucharest Information on 129.400.

properties.Name: TARGA
properties.description:
Area's South-West Entry/Exit Point

Recommended ENTRY procedure
When flying over TARGA, you should initiate contact with Strejnic Airfield on 131.455 and wait to receive the flight conditions in the area. Entry through this point is performed at 1400ft QNH. The next report from incoming traffic in order to enter south traffic pattern should be made before downwind if runway in use is 25, or before base if runway in use is 07, unless otherwise instructed by the flight coordinator. 

Recommended EXIT procedure
Leaving the traffic pattern is usually done right before joining the base leg if runway in use is 07, or just before joining dowwind, if runway in use is 25, following the way to TARGA in an ascending flight towards a minimum of 1700ft QNH. At the vertical of the locality of Târgușoru Vechi, contact Bucharest Information on 129.400.

properties.Name: DARMA
properties.description:
Area's West Entry/Exit point Point

Recommended ENTRY procedure
When flying over DARMA, you should initiate contact with Strejnic Airfield on 131.455 and wait to receive the flight conditions in the area. Entry through this point is performed at 1500ft QNH. The next report from incoming traffic in order to join traffic pattern should be made over the airfield's runway, unless otherwise instructed by the flight coordinator. Entry into the traffic pattern is usually made near the power station. 

Recommended EXIT procedure
Leaving the traffic pattern is usually done from the downwind leg or base leg if runway in use is 07, or directly from upwind if runway in use is 25, following the way to DARMA in an ascending flight towards a minimum of 2000ft QNH. At the vertical of the locality of Dărmănești, contact Bucharest Information on 129.400.

Area no. 1
properties.description:
It is located vertically above the aerodrome and enclosed within a circle with a 1 km radius, centered at the aerodrome reference point.

In this area, aircraft flights are restricted south of the Strejnicu - Ploiești road.

Within this area, the following flights can be conducted: training flights, maneuverability flights, technical flights, calibration flights, aerobatic flights, formation flights, demonstration flights, airshows, parachute jump flights, and glider flights.

For regular flights, a recommended minimum working altitude of 2500ft QNH/ 2000ft QFE is advised, corresponding to vertical separation from aircraft taking off and landing.

properties.Name: Area no. 3
properties.description:
It is located 3 km from the reference point in the magnetic direction of 240º - 060°.

It is enclosed within an irregular polygon defined by the following alignments:

To the North:
The line connecting the northwestern boundary of Târgsoru Nou to the intersection of the Strejnicu - Crângu lui Bot Forest road with the Ploiești - Târgoviște railway.

To the East:
The line connecting the intersection of the Strejnicu - Crângu lui Bot Forest road with the Ploiești - Târgoviște railway to the branching point of the main road in Strejnicu towards the west (near the school).

To the South:
The line connecting the branching point of the main road in Strejnicu towards the west (near the school) to the northwestern boundary of Târgsoru Vechi.

To the West :
The line connecting the northwestern boundary of Târgșoru Vechi to the northwestern boundary of Târgșoru Nou.

In this area, training flights, maneuverability flights, calibration flights, aerobatic flights, formation flights, and glider flights are conducted.

A minimum working altitude of 2500ft QNH/ 2000ft QFE is recommended in this area.
